1).Single Inheritance Programe.

package practice_java;//single inheritance

class college
{
	 int num_stu;
}
class cce extends college
{
	void display()
	{
		System.out.println("Student number: "+num_stu);
	}
}
public class inheritance 
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
    	cce obj=new cce();
    	obj.num_stu=3;
    	obj.display();
    }
}
 Output:
Student number: 3

2).wap to to implement a following :Hierarchial inheritance

package practice_java;

class Car {
    String color = "black";

    void display() {
        System.out.println("The color of car: " + color);
    }
}

class Honda extends Car {
   
}

class BMW extends Car {
   
}

class Skoda extends Car {
   
}

public class carbrand {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car ob1 = new Honda();
        ob1.color = "blue";
        ob1.display();  

        Car ob2 = new BMW();
        ob2.color = "red";
        ob2.display();  

        Car ob3 = new Skoda();
        ob3.color = "white";
        ob3.display(); 
    }
}

OUTPUT:
The color of car: blue
The color of car: red
The color of car: white

3)//create a class name exam with the feelings namely maths,english and java.These are all the subject names.Derieve  a class total and using the method print and print the total

package practice_java;
class Subject
{
	public int mark;
}
class Maths extends Subject
{
	public void display()
	{
		System.out.println("The Maths Mark is: "+mark);
	}
}
class English extends Subject
{
	public void display()
	{
		System.out.println("The English Mark is: "+mark);
	}
}
class Java extends Subject
{
	public void display()
	{
		System.out.println("The Java Mark is: "+mark);
	}
}
public class Exam {

	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Maths obj1=new Maths();
		English obj2=new English();
		Java obj3=new Java();
		obj1.mark=95;
		obj2.mark=85;
		obj3.mark=100;
		obj1.display();
		obj2.display();
		obj3.display();	
	}

}
output:
The Maths Mark is: 95
The English Mark is: 85
The Java Mark is: 100
